snippet.textDisplay: Why is everyone all "OH SPACEX IS BETTER ULA TRASH" I personally like both, Just because SpaceX lands a booster and ULA doesn't does not make one superior, These are both private companies completely separate and they do things their own way. Now, how about next time you say ULA is bad think of all the time and effort engineers have dedicated their life to. SpaceX has a different concept and base all their research into one thing, reusability. ULA was made way longer ago when the tech wasn't around. What's more logical, Spend millions of dollars to revamp and possibly make new spacecraft that are more reusable and put hundreds of R&D hours into it, or use the same heavily reliable fleet that is affordable for larger companies that may need ULA's services. I think they stick with the same fleet. I know this sounds greedy but please like so this can get to peoples attention.
